<DocsLayout title="CI Integration" description="Set up automated behavior drift detection in your pipeline.">

<h2>How it works</h2>
<ol>
  <li>Generate a spec with <code>pecto init --output specs.yaml</code></li>
  <li>Commit <code>specs.yaml</code> to your repo</li>
  <li>In CI, run <code>pecto verify specs.yaml</code></li>
  <li>If the code's behavior has changed without updating the spec, the build fails (exit code 1)</li>
</ol>

<h2>GitHub Actions</h2>

<h3>Simple setup</h3>
<pre><code>name: Behavior Check

on: [push, pull_request]

jobs:
  pecto:
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest
    steps:
      - uses: actions/checkout@v4

      - name: Install pecto
        run: cargo install pecto

      - name: Verify behavior spec
        run: pecto verify specs.yaml</code></pre>

<h3>Using the pecto action</h3>
<pre><code>- uses: AliciaMartinelli/pecto/.github/actions/pecto@main
  with:
    spec-file: specs.yaml
    path: .
    language: auto</code></pre>

<p>The action caches the pecto binary for faster subsequent runs.</p>

<h2>Exit codes</h2>
<table>
  <thead><tr><th>Code</th><th>Meaning</th></tr></thead>
  <tbody>
    <tr><td><code>0</code></td><td>Spec matches code — no drift</td></tr>
    <tr><td><code>1</code></td><td>Spec has drifted — behavior changed</td></tr>
    <tr><td><code>non-zero</code></td><td>Error (file not found, parse error, etc.)</td></tr>
  </tbody>
</table>

<h2>Workflow: keeping specs up to date</h2>

<p>When <code>pecto verify</code> fails in CI:</p>

<ol>
  <li>Run <code>pecto init --output specs.yaml</code> locally to regenerate</li>
  <li>Review the diff: <code>git diff specs.yaml</code></li>
  <li>If the behavior change is intentional, commit the updated spec</li>
  <li>If unintentional, fix the code</li>
</ol>

<h2>PR Behavior Comments</h2>
<p>Auto-post a behavior diff as a comment on every pull request. Shows new, modified, and removed endpoints, entities, and dependencies.</p>

<pre><code># .github/workflows/pecto-pr.yml
name: Behavior Diff
on: pull_request

jobs:
  diff:
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest
    steps:
      - uses: actions/checkout@v4
        with:
          fetch-depth: 0
      - uses: AliciaMartinelli/pecto/.github/actions/pecto-pr@main
        with:
          github-token: $&#123;&#123; secrets.GITHUB_TOKEN &#125;&#125;</code></pre>

<p>The action automatically finds and updates its previous comment (no duplicates). The <code>&lt;!-- pecto --&gt;</code> marker in the comment is used for identification.</p>

<h2>Architecture Rules in CI</h2>
<p><code>pecto check</code> validates architecture fitness rules. Exit code 1 if any rule fails.</p>

<pre><code>- name: Check architecture rules
  run: pecto check --rules .pecto/rules.yaml</code></pre>

<p>Configure rules in <code>.pecto/rules.yaml</code>:</p>
<pre><code>rules:
  no-circular-dependencies: true
  controllers-no-direct-db-access: true
  all-endpoints-need-authentication: true
  max-service-dependencies: 5</code></pre>

<h2>Comparing PRs</h2>
<p>Use <code>pecto diff</code> or <code>pecto pr-diff</code> in PR reviews to see behavior changes:</p>

<pre><code>- name: Show behavior changes (raw)
  run: pecto diff origin/main HEAD

- name: Show behavior changes (markdown)
  run: pecto pr-diff origin/main HEAD</code></pre>

<h2>Tips</h2>
<ul>
  <li>Use <code>--quiet</code> flag when piping output in scripts</li>
  <li>Store specs in a <code>specs/</code> directory for multi-module projects</li>
  <li>Add <code>specs.yaml</code> to your PR template checklist: "Did you update the behavior spec?"</li>
</ul>

